[{"category":"section","location":"#Suslin","page":"Home","text":"Constructive elementary-matrix factorizations for small supported SL_3 slices over polynomial rings.","title":"Suslin"},{"category":"section","location":"#Example","page":"Home","text":"using Suslin, Oscar\n\nR, (X,) = Oscar.polynomial_ring(QQ, [\"X\"])\nA = matrix(R, [\n    one(R)      one(R) + X      zero(R);\n    X           one(R) + X + X^2 zero(R);\n    zero(R)     zero(R)         one(R)\n])\n\nfactors = elementary_factorization(A)\nverify_factorization(A, factors)","title":"Example"},{"category":"section","location":"#Scope","page":"Home","text":"elementary_factorization(A) currently supports only a narrow 3x3 univariate SL_3 slice.\nverify_factorization(A, factors) checks exact multiplication against A.\nThe implementation is staged and does not yet cover the full theorem.","title":"Scope"},{"category":"section","location":"#References","page":"Home","text":"Park and Woodburn, An algorithmic proof of Suslin's stability theorem for polynomial rings.\nLogar and Sturmfels, Algorithms for the Quillen-Suslin theorem.\nFitchas and Galligo, Nullstellensatz effectif et conjecture de Serre.\n\n","title":"References"}]
